1. Load and update rds file

se <- readRDS('../data/processed_AB_20230627/salmon.merged.gene_counts.rds')
colinfo <- data.frame(colData(se))
colinfo <- colinfo %>% 
  mutate(site = case_when(
    endsWith(names, "Nor") ~ "Norm",
    endsWith(names, "Norm") ~ "Norm",
    endsWith(names, "Pol") ~ "Poly",
    endsWith(names, "Poly") ~ "Poly")) %>%
  mutate(patient = str_split_fixed(names, fixed("_"), 3)[,2])
se$tissue <-colinfo[,3] # add tissue info
se$donor <- colinfo[,4] #add patients info
head(colData(se))

# save as DESeqDataSet object
dds <- DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(countData = assay(se, 'round_counts'),
                              colData = colData(se),
                              design = ~ tissue)

2. Data pre-processing

2.1 Filter out low expressed genes

plot(table(rowSums(counts(dds)==0)), 
     xlab = "Number of samples with unexpressed genes across all samples",
     ylab = "Number of genes")

# act conservatively - only filter out genes with less than 2 count across all samples
keep <- rowSums(counts(dds)) > 2
dds <- dds[keep,]
nrow(dds)
## [1] 32450
plot(table(rowSums(counts(dds)==0)), 
     xlab = "Number of samples with unexpressed genes across all samples",
     ylab = "Number of genes")

library(RColorBrewer)
nsamples <- ncol(dds)
col <- brewer.pal(nsamples, 'Paired')
## Warning in brewer.pal(nsamples, "Paired"): n too large, allowed maximum for palette Paired is 12
## Returning the palette you asked for with that many colors
plot(density(counts(dds)), 
     col=col[1], 
     main="", 
     xlab="",
     log='y')
## Warning in xy.coords(x, y, xlabel, ylabel, log): 76 y values <= 0 omitted from
## logarithmic plot
for (i in 2:nsamples){
  den <- density(counts(dds)[,i])
  lines(den$x, den$y, col=col[i], lwd=2)
  }

2.2 Log transformation

rld <- rlog(dds, blind = T)
## rlog() may take a few minutes with 30 or more samples,
## vst() is a much faster transformation
head(assay(rld))[1:5, 1:5]
